I have written bash-scripts for ClamAV containers in which I have downloaded 100 viruses and use ClamAV to search for viruses in the particular directory. 
For Ubuntu and Debian, bash scripts are the same and for the alpine container, there is done some necessary changes so that scripts can work.
Please let me know if these scripts require some changes.
@kmehant, @charithccmc, @ravindudsilva

pr_body:
In this PR I have created dummy deployment files which includes
1. master-nodeport.yaml which directs request to master pod to port 80 where Nginx is listening.
2. master.yaml which includes configuration of two containers one is Nginx and another is alpine(which will be used to get IP of slave nodes using headless service).
3. slave-headless.yaml which will help to get pod IP.
4. slave.yaml which is running alpine image. 

I have not used the busy box container due to some errors and it is not able to get the IP address of slave containers.
I am now implementing HPA on slave nodes.
I have used Nginx because I have to check if nodeport is working or not.
